---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---
<Base title="About — Mad Learning Lab" description="We build evaluation frameworks and capacity-building programs that program managers can actually run, maintain, and adapt.">
  <section class="page">
    <p class="page-eyebrow">About</p>
    <h2 class="page-title">Created out of chaos, sticking around with purpose.</h2>
    <p>
      We started Mad Learning Lab in 2025, after years of watching the same pattern repeat at
      organization after organization: when budgets tightened, the work of understanding whether
      programs actually worked was the first thing cut. The need to prove impact only grew
      louder. The capacity to do it kept shrinking.
    </p>
    <p>
      Program teams don't need another 80-page logic model from an outside consultant. They need
      an evaluation system a busy program manager can actually run, maintain, and adapt as their
      work changes.
    </p>
    <p>
      That's what we build. Frameworks sized for the people who use them, paired with training
      so teams can keep measuring what matters on their own. When we leave, the work stays.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="founder">
    <div class="founder-body">
      <p class="page-eyebrow">Founder</p>
      <h3 class="founder-name">Madeleine Smith, MPA</h3>
      <p>
        Madeleine has spent eight years inside nonprofits, working with the people who run the
        programs and the funders who pay for them. Across that work, the same pattern kept
        showing up: every data system, reporting framework, and governance structure had
        something quietly broken — usually for the people who relied on it most.
      </p>
      <p>
        She founded Mad Learning Lab to fix that pattern, one organization at a time. Her work
        focuses on understanding what's getting in the way, building what's missing, and handing
        it back in a form the team can actually run themselves.
      </p>
      <p class="founder-meta">
        Based in San Francisco. <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/madeleineesmith" target="_blank" rel="noopener">LinkedIn →</a>
      </p>
    </div>
    <img class="founder-portrait" src="/founder.png" alt="Madeleine Smith" />
  </section>

  <section class="page team">
    <p class="page-eyebrow">Our Team of Consultants</p>
    <h3 class="team-title">A small core, supported by a deep bench.</h3>
    <p>
      Mad Learning Lab keeps a small, intentional footprint. When a project calls for additional
      capacity — specialized methodology, subject-matter depth, or extra analytic hands — we
      bring in independent consultants from a network of trusted collaborators built over years
      of working in the field.
    </p>
    <p>
      It's how we stay nimble and personal while taking on work that needs more than one set of
      hands.
    </p>
  </section>
</Base>
